gomodel:SYNGO_1189  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The data in figure 5 shows the involvement of GRASP-1 (GRIPAP1) in the transport of postsynaptic RER into the spine.. Experimental description: from M&M; \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) rat brains\"\n\n\"Anti-GRASP-1 (#5285) was generated by immunizing rabbits with GST-GRASP-1(1-378) and used for immuno electronmicroscopy.\"\n\n\"The rat GRASP-1 (accession NM_053807) smartpool siRNA (cat# L-096315-01) was from Dharmacon\".\nNCBI GenBank accession NM_053807 confirms GRASP-1 streetname refers to gene GRIPAP1.\n\n\"GRASP-1 truncation constructs and GRASP-1 mutant lacking aa280-300 were made with PCR from full-length GRASP-1 cDNA 1 [28]. GRASP-1* rescue constructs were prepared by a PCR-based strategy to introduce four silent substitutions in the target site. The target sequence GCTCTCTGAGAAATTGAAA was modified into GCTTTCGGAAAAGTTGAAA.\"\n\nNucleotide BLAST of this sequence confirmed this is gene GRIPAP1." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1189" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

